HEADWORD: Turnip-shell
<hw>Tur"nip-shell"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several large, thick, spiral marine shells belonging to
<gen>Rapa</gen> and allied genera, somewhat turnip-shaped.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

